  "tune": "Melita",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "My hope is built on nothing less Than Jesus&#39; blood and righteousness. I dare not trust the sweetest frame, But wholly trust in Jesus&#39; Name. On Christ the solid Rock I stand, All other ground is sinking sand.",
    "v2": "When darkness veils His lovely face, I rest on His unchanging grace. In every high and stormy gale, My anchor holds within the veil. Rock I stand, All other ground is sinking sand.",
    "v3": "His oath, His cove- nant, His blood, Support me in the whelming flood. When all around my soul gives way, He then is all my hope and stay. Rock I stand, All other ground is sinking sand.",
    "v4": "When He shall come with trumpet sound, Oh may I then in Him be found. Dressed in His righteousness alone, Faultless to stand before the throne. Rock I stand, All other ground is sinking sand."
  },
